reviews.text: Lots of fun during holidays and "Art in the Park" during the summer time. Great for kids and pets too. The traffic can be a bit heavy sometimes so keep an eye on the little ones.

We went during Christmas and were amazed to see all the lighting. This was not even part of our trip to begin with. We just heard it from a friend in passing and thought we will go check it out. We were totally in for a shocking surprise. It was like a fairy tale land with all the lights and all the colors. A must visit place around Christmas.

One of my fav spots in WA...

I always found the story of how this Bavarian-style Village came about interesting, it wasn’t because there were German settlers, but it all started as the city’s revitalization project in the 1960’s.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I love visiting this place for hikes, food, wine tastings, and doing it all with the picture perfect backdrop. 😊
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Also, a little known fact: Leavenworth is #1 pear grower in US! As shown in one of the pics here, in May, you’ll see the pear blossoms covering the hill all around, it’s a sight worth seeing, but only lasts for a week or two.
Lots of cool stores in the area. Plenty of things to do for all families. Couple of stores are bakeries, fudge shops, and wine cellars as an example. You won't be dissapointed.
Beautiful mountains surrounding you, fun shops to browse and plenty of places to eat, have a beer or a glass of wine.

I was very disappointed with the fact that both google and iPhone maps were telling me two very different location points (for the address stated above) at which the theater was at neither one! We were calling the theater since 5pm with no answer or anyone to talk to. It’s frustrating paying for 6tickets, missing the show, and poor information on their website. Better customer service please!

Sound of Music is one of the best summer shows we've ever seen.  There isn't a theater in any major city that can compete with the outdoor setting tucked in the trees, breathtaking mountain views in the background and as night falls the stars light the night sky.  The actors were spot on with their voices and acting and the orchestra nailed it.  Our seats and view of the stage was excellent even though we sat near the back.

They do have a snack bar that is open during intermission and at the beginning of the show.  

Great job!
Great productions in a beautiful outdoor setting.

attended Bye Bye Birdie show at the fish hatchery on a Thursday evening.  Great show and cast. Rent a $1 seat cushion your bottom will thank you. The worse part of the whole experience is the parking and getting to your car after the performance.  No one directing traffic, no lights and plenty of dust.  I hated that they have special parking for handicap as almost everyone using that area could clearly walk fine and after the performance these same people sped thru the parking area with no regard for those of us having to walk further to our car.  Just a bad experience. If you can park close to the exit and be fast out of your seat you have a chance. We were walking with slow pokes so we got stuck in a big mess of traffic.
I have been many times to see the sound of music and loved it each time! No one should miss this! Very well done and the setting it beautiful.

A majestic park filled with lovely overhanging trees, awe-inspiring views of the harbor, and a relaxing trail for walking. There are many great spots to relax and read. And of course, you can't miss the iconic pineapple fountain. Just a wonderful time.

This area is the perfect spot to bring your family for outdoor activities. We enjoyed a picnic on the grass overlooking the water and the kids ran around playing chase after. We flew our drone for awhile and got some gorgeous footage. Lots of beautiful scenery and on weekends break dancers and musical  artists can be found performing. Definitely recommend for some family fun.

The fountain is spectacular. It's nice and easy going. Not much else to do but it's not far from downtown. It would be great to have a botanical garden or planetarium at the park that served cocktails, but I'm just dreaming here.

Waterfront Park was the perfect spot to hang out while our family waited for our reservation time at Fleet Landing.  Lots of space for our kids to run and play and for us to rest in the sun.  Had it been warmer, they would have really enjoyed wading in the fountain.  We made sure to get a family picture in front of the pineapple fountain, too.  Be sure to stop here along your family's travels, too!

This is such a great place for a romantic walk on the water. There is a nice pier with picnic tables for a great lunch or early dinner. The famous Pineapple Fountain is here. There are several fountains for kids to run around in during the hot summers. It's a great place to visit and definitely worth taking the time to see.

This is our main store for shopping close to home! It can be pretty spendy at times with prices, but with Just4U coupons help a lot!! They have some great deals at times. If you want quality and a variety even with Safeway brands  Safeway is great for that. They have a deli, bakery and pharmacy. They also have a Starbucks inside. The one complaint I have lately with them is their meat department. The quality of their meat isn't as great as it use to be. We've found bone grit on the pork and bones in boneless skinless chicken. Otherwise I love their produce, breads, desserts and products!! Plus you'll always get GREAT customer service and asked if you need help out!! Or you can also do self checkout instead.

All and all it's not a bad place to shop... it's a little spendy... you definitely need to watch for deals... The cashiers are pretty nice..The pharmacy and their employees are Rock Stars... Trevor is one of the pharmacist who always goes above and beyond to take care of your needs... Thank you ever so much Trevor... yes, Amy your pretty awesome... Thank you kindly... :-) :-) :-)

This store is brightly lit and well maintained. We usually go to Costco for a lot of reasons but for small and unique grocery purchases we end up at Safeway. The checkers at this location are almost always pleasant and attentive, both things that aren't always guaranteed these days.
Its a grocery store chain. The quality is good. The price is a little high, but they offer a membership discount.

The old lady in the deli is absolutely the rudest person I’ve ever met in my life she constantly makes you feel like your bothering her that you want a sandwhich rolled her eyes and got huffy puffy that I asked for bacon and proceeded to say “I guess, but that’s gonna cost more” (like I didn’t already know that) then didn’t ask me if I wanted anything else threw my snadwhich on the counter and walked away. I will never be going back there again so disappointed

Their food is home made and the quality is very good. Its family owned and operated. They come off as very caring and concerned about making a good product. Their online page does not do the place justice. Probably the best quality food you can get in Leavenworth that has not been frozen first.
Amazing, delicious, healthy local breakfast, lunch, lattes and fresh pressed juices. Vegetarian and gluten free options. Outdoor seating available and a great indoor atmosphere. A Leavenworth staple.

Best fresh food in Leavenworth!! Looking for gluten free & vegan, delicious salads and soups with fresh ingredients , fruit & veggie smoothies and juices ?!?! This is the place! I stop here every time I drive through Leavenworth .

From fresh juices to vegan pastries, this place does it right. It is a locally owned business that would make the whole community pout if it were ever to go away! If you're looking for a quick bite, this small cozy venue has you covered! Make sure you try their pastries!

What a great spot! Great homemade pastries every day, I tried the Strawberry Rhubarb coffeecake and it was incredible! Friendly staff and a wonderful place to enjoy the morning. Would definitely recommend checking this spot out if you are in town!

Enjoyed the sunshine last weekend by taking driving to Leavenworth to have lunch @ Munchen Haus with a cool beverage. We enjoyed a pretty nice lunch with great conversations with folks we met there.
Awesome sausages with an elaborate array of condiments including sauerkraut.
Each table has warming fires if cool enough.

Great food! I love having all the fun mustard choices! The seating is outside, and though the environment is great and they offer some ways to keep you warm, it's not my first choice in the winter or colder months. They also have some decent beer choices on tap. You should at least check this place out!

We came. We saw. We sampled almost every mustard. We sat - at the most glorious (bench style) table. We ate - so good. We left - all good things come to an end. Going back tomorrow!

Back to the table, it doubled as a fire pit which kept us warm while we mulled over the menu and while we enjoyed delicious brats. The menu had plenty of options, but thankfully not too many options. I get overwhelmed by too many choices.

LOVE LOVE LOVE this place! 
So much so that I really wanna take one star away for the really long queue but I loved this place too much to do that. 

If you are a beer enthusiast, look no further! This place, the food, the beer, the ambience: everything is just epic. 

Especially if you visit around Christmas when everything is lit up, just be sure you dress up with extra layers and you will totally enjoy the place. The seating is in open but if you are lucky, you might find a nice warm spot near a heater.  

QUEUE: The queue for the food is ridiculously long. 

SEATING: Could get crowded and you might end up sharing benches with strangers. I know it sounds bad but it really wouldn’t make much of a difference.

PRICE: Not too much. Value for money especially considering the fact that it is a tourist place. 

TIP: If you are driving, be extra extra careful as the roads are treacherous in winters. A 4x4 vehicle especially with winter tyres and perhaps a set of chains in the trunk is a good idea. Also, LAYER UP LAYER UP!

Must visit if in Leavenworth, for the vibe, food, beer, and food...and food. If you can get a table upstairs with a view of the surrounding area, it's worth the extra chill. Never been here when it wasn't crowded, so prepare yourself for that in advance. Get adventurous with their brats as well! Don't be afraid to sample some of the varieties that you'll never find most places.

Great food and service. Fantastic musician named Paul Sweeney played any song the patrons asked for. It made a good evening really great. However, we were really disappointed to learn that Paul had to pay for his own beer tab. We paid it for him. No bar should charge their entertainer...they are who bring the people in...

Great food, fair prices, friendly service. This was our first restaurant experience in Leavenworth. We wanted something authentic and German. Baren Haus has a nice old-style building with plenty of room. Their menu selection was small but fair, but their prices were a bit higher considering what we got. The food was great, but not quite what we had hoped for.

This bar/restaurant is a fantastic! I was shocked to see how busy staff were an the server never neglected to check up on us, making sure we were taken care. Serves was excellent an also the food Fantastisch!

Have had lunch here every time I’ve visited Leavenworth.  The service is really great, and the food has been good every time.  It might not be the same as the food I’ve had when I visited Germany, but I never really expected it to be the same.  The dinner bread they serve and the garlic butter are great.  Ordered the Schnitzel and combination platter. Recommend.

Figure about $20/plate. I had the schnitzel because it's my first German food experience. My wife had a sirloin burger. Both were good but nothing to write home about. The wait staff was pleasant and service was prompt

Blewett Brewing Company has become a staple in our Leavenworth trips. The pizza is absolutely amazing and is a great break from the basic. Their unique creations keep us enjoying something new every time we visit. The beer is always great and they have plenty of IPA options to keep us happy. They have a Crowler machine, so we are able to take 32oz cans to go and share with friends. The setup is great, we can eat in the restaurant area when we have our son, or we can sit at the bar when it's just my wife and I. The staff is fun and friendly and always makes us feel at home when we pop in. Cheers!

Brewery has a dining area (kids allowed) and a separate bar area (21+). For a small brewery the beer is very good! they have very good beer selection. We stopped in for some beers ended up buying a sampler and 2 pizzas! the pizza is amazing as well. Tucked away a couple blocks out of the main street in Leavenworth it’s a great place to drink a beer away from all the people!

Cozy, romantic, great food. Had the winter salad and added sausage to a classic pepperoni, both were exceptionally good. This is a small pizza place that I have been to twice now, once with my two young kids and once with just my wife. It's a kid friendly place, but I would venture it's more catered to an older crowd. I will continue to return to Blewett each time we visit Leavenworth.
Loved their pizza! Seriously good. Even classics like pepperoni and margarita tasted amazing.

Great atmosphere, drinks, and PIZZA!

Blewett has good drink pairings, and my mouth is salivating just thinking about the pizza. The only drink I didn't care for was the experimental drink... It needs a lot more tweaking. Pizza wise, I ordered the Sweet Daddy because let's face it, who doesn't want a sweet daddy? The zesty bbq chicken, smoked red onion, thick-cut bacon, aged mozzarella, chives, and parmesan hit the tastebuds just right. I don't typically like crust, but the soft bread was very flavorful. 

All and all the prices are good, the service is speedy, and portions fit one to two people.

Delicious food and great service. The food was really quite good, with plenty of vegetarian friendly options and quality drinks in addition. The service was some of the fastest I've  experienced! Make sure to make a reservation if you come during a busy tourist time.

Had a couple of drinks with friend and a few mini tacos they call it and the tab was more expensive than having a nice dinner with a love one. Pretty expensive for what it is. The bar was pretty small, bartender made the drinks pretty good, food was just okay.

Its surprisingly much better than many other Latin influenced restaurants in Seattle. Food is tasty with good portion, all you can eat salsas are pretty interesting but kids menu is where more options are needed.
Space is little small and cozy, however staff is very friendly and service is pretty amazing.
TIP - book your table in advance, wait time goes over an hour during peak evening hours.

This place was awesome! It was busy both nights we were in town. The music isn't too loud but the noise of everyone talking in a smaller eating space. It's good food! We had the stuffed peppers and the sauce saw great. The wet burrito was great! I had the burrito cubano and that was good too.

Great customer service and delicious food. 😋
You can tell that a lot of thought and care goes into their food. It’s was worth the time and money every time I come here. 😊

Hands down the best place to eat in Leavenworth!!! I was so happy to find a restaurant that matched the entire theme of the town. The staff dress so cute! They serve amazing German beer and the menu is very appetizing. The pretzel cheese they offer was also the best I found in the world of Leavenworth. I loved it so much I ate there twice during my two day stay! I look forward to my return to the special place.

Excellent place.  Love the decor and the ultra cozy booths.  Food is amazing and the schnitzel is the size of your head so come hungry.  Super friendly staff as well.  One of the best restaurants Leavenworth has to offer.

German inspired menu. Schnitzel Cordon bleu  was very tasty as was the Chicken Schnitzel sandwich with German potato salad. Fairly pricey with 1 item from the diner menu  and 1 from the lunch menu with 1 shared beer $72.00. Lunch is served until 4 pm. Young staff was friendly.  Located down stairs on the main street.

If you go to a Germany town, do not forget their sausage, and plus a pork trotters.

If you go to this restaurant, do not forget to remember its atmosphere and decoration. Old style, but impressive in a whole. 

They must have a good chief. The flavor is so good that I’d like to be there again, and have a big bite on the sausage.

We left without a single complaint! The food was delicious! The atmosphere was well lit, filled with live accordion music, and the staff were all friendly and welcoming. We were checked on consistently, but not in an intrusive way. Without a doubt we can not return to Leavenworth without a stop for dinner here again.
